ld potentially use the audio studios, maybe, and record your own podcast for a small fee….which could diversify the stream of content on your public media station. And you’d be in a space that would become sustainable because you’d want to share what you learned there…and because you’d feel comfortable there….and you’d want to see that space continue to flourish.","markups":[]},{"name":"9d08","type":4,"text":"","markups":[],"layout":4,"metadata":{"id":"1*S4xsXqzVnI-rxvhA-L7whg.png","originalWidth":1120,"originalHeight":666}},{"name":"2fb9","type":1,"text":"I want people to think of public media stations as public spaces. But people are already expanding public media into public space. In Chicago, producer Jenn Brandel invites folks to submit questions they have about Chicago — and then people vote on which ones they want answered. The people who originally asked them questions then go out with reporters to find the answers.","markups":[{"type":3,"start":165,"end":198,"href":"http://curiouscity.wbez.org/","title":"","rel":""},{"type":1,"start":0,"end":66}]},{"name":"41fe","type":1,"text":"And in New Orleans, the station has set up Listenings Posts around the city. Each week, they pose a question which people can answer, directly from a barber shop and two libraries. The answers are then integrated into a show on air.","markups":[{"type":3,"start":24,"end":59,"href":"http://wwno.org/programs/listening-post?page=1","title":"","rel":""}]},{"name":"facc","type":4,"text":"","markups":[],"layout":1,"metadata":{"id":"1*nA1dSIF2J2FXg7GLJfW7lg.png","originalWidth":717,"originalHeight":388}},{"name":"d58d","type":1,"text":"I also think about projects that are like the things public media does. To me, Humans of New York is public media — where someone goes out and tells stories, deeply personal stories of people all over the world. Sharing snippets of their lives and making us all think about each other.","markups":[]},{"name":"1487","type":1,"text":"It’s also Code Academy, where people can gain knowledge and learn more about the world, for free, through code.","markups":[]},{"name":"f82a","type":4,"text":"","markups":[],"layout":4,"metadata":{"id":"1*8eFPMKwvGMFW9js8PtZKNQ.png","originalWidth":532,"originalHeight":539}},{"name":"af21","type":1,"text":"It’s Reddit, where in the NPR community you can badge yourself with local member station flair and then find other people from where you live and take about issues you care about.","markups":[]},{"name":"4937","type":1,"text":"And it’s the Creative Action Network, where designers can volunteer to create things for non-profits and further their own reach and make money at the same time.","markups":[]},{"name":"1135","type":1,"text":"","markups":[]},{"name":"35e6","type":1,"text":"But these projects largely take place in people’s homes, where they’re not connected to each other. I think we can better connect people to each other — and to public media — by inviting them into our spaces and giving them the opportunity — as the public — to use the spaces that we have around the country. And people can learn skills and share knowledge and give back…in ways that will strengthen the communities we live in.","markups":[{"type":1,"start":100,"end":427}]},{"name":"96fa","type":1,"text":"I want people to deeply care about public media because I think it’s important that we have news that engages and informs and is open to all. Public media will never go behind a paywall. And there are ways to pledge support in all sorts of ways — and I believe that by expanding what membership means…and how to become one… we can strengthen our communities and ourselves while also strengthening public radio too.","markups":[{"type":1,"start":142,"end":187},{"type":1,"start":324,"end":414}]},{"name":"2860","type":1,"text":"Please fill out this form to find out more and/or help out.","markups":[{"type":3,"start":0,"end":58,"href":"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1xwvY7GB3uI17AWgZbMljsQOfr8zWNzfPxG_6AEPS4NY/viewform?usp=se